			<step>       <!-- Recipe steps -->
			Heat the water for the pasta.
Start by preparing the ingredients:
Chop the garlic, ginger and shallot.
Cut the zucchini, bell pepper and broccoli into small cubes.
When the water boils, add the noodles and cook for 5 minutes, or as long as you normally cook your noodles. They should not be too soft.
Heat the oil in a wok.
When it's very hot, quickly fry the ginger, then add the garlic and shallot.
Immediately add the zucchini pieces and cover for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If the mixture tends to burn, add a little more water.
Remove the noodles from the water, drain slightly and add to the wok mixture.
Add the bell pepper and broccoli pieces and 3 tablespoons of soy sauce. Cover for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add sashimi sauce or classic wok sauce and stir.
Cook until water has almost evaporated.
Serve hot in bowls with chopsticks.
