			<step>        <!-- Recipe steps -->
			Blend the raspberries and strain to remove the seeds.
Add a dash of lemon juice to soften the acidity.
Add 10 g of sugar to the raspberry pulp and blend. Set aside.
Start whipping the egg whites until stiff. At the same time, prepare a sugar syrup with 30 g water and 80 g sugar.
As soon as the mixture begins to bubble, stop cooking.
Drizzle in the sugar syrup while continuing to whisk the egg whites. The texture should be smooth and shiny.
Incorporate the raspberry pulp and mix again until you obtain an airy mousse.
